\det(M)=0
\det(A)\leq0
 A= \begin{pmatrix}  M  & F \\  F  & M \end{pmatrix} 
 M= \begin{pmatrix} 0 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 \end{pmatrix}\quad F = \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 \\ 0 & 1 \end{pmatrix} 
 \det \begin{pmatrix} M & F \\ F & M \end{pmatrix}=1 
\det\begin{pmatrix}  M  & F \\  F  & M \end{pmatrix}=\det(M-F)\det(M+F),
\det\begin{pmatrix}  0  & F \\  F  & 0 \end{pmatrix}=(\det F)^2.
