\det M=0
M-F
M+F
M=\begin{pmatrix}  a  & a \\  a  & a \end{pmatrix}, F=\begin{pmatrix}  0  & -b \\  b  & 0 \end{pmatrix}
(M-F)=(M+F)^T=\begin{pmatrix}  a  & a+b \\  a-b  & a \end{pmatrix}\text{ has real eigenvalues }a\pm\sqrt{a^2-b^2}>0\text{ if }0<b<a.
\begin{pmatrix}  a & a & 0 & -b \\  a & a & b & 0 \\  0 & -b & a & a \\  b & 0 & a & a \end{pmatrix}\text{ has (double) real eigenvalues }a\pm\sqrt{a^2-b^2}>0\text{ if }0<b<a.
